  "notes": "Amis (Pangcah) — the largest Formosan (Austronesian) language of Taiwan, written in the official romanised orthography promulgated by Taiwan's Council of Indigenous Peoples. Practical orthography: /ts/ = ⟨c⟩, /j/ = ⟨y⟩, /ʡ/ = ⟨ʼ⟩, /ʔ/ = ⟨^⟩, /ɮ/ = ⟨d⟩, /ŋ/ = ⟨ng⟩, /ʜ/ = ⟨x⟩, /v/ = ⟨f⟩, /ɺ/ = ⟨l⟩. Three-vowel system /i a u/ (⟨o⟩ and ⟨u⟩ both write /u/); ⟨e⟩ writes a short schwa of uncertain phonemic status.",
